	shinkawa ltd
	
Shinkawa Ltd. Announces Consolidated and Nonconsolidated Earnings Results for the Year Ended March 31, 2017
Jun 12 17
Shinkawa Ltd. announced consolidated and nonconsolidated earnings results for the year ended March 31, 2017. For the year, on consolidated basis, the company reported net sales of JPY 16,438 million compared to JPY 12,662 million a year ago. Operating income was JPY 294 million. Ordinary income was JPY 432 million. Profit before income taxes was JPY 478 million. Profit attributable to owners of the parent was JPY 243 million compared to loss of JPY 1,849 million a year ago. Profit per share was JPY 13.37 compared to loss of JPY 101.75 a year ago.

For the year, on nonconsolidated basis, the company reported net sales of JPY 14,991 million, operating loss of JPY 604 million, ordinary loss of JPY 442 million, loss before income taxes of JPY 83 million, net loss of JPY 87 million.


Shinkawa Ltd. to Release Package Bonder for Multiple Processes
May 12 17
Shinkawa Ltd. has developed the FPB-1ws NeoForce for wafer and substrate as the second step in the multi-process package bonder FPB series, and started accepting new orders. The FPB series is a bonder that has significantly enhanced productivity (2.4 times/machine compared with other company's models), which was a challenge for thermal compression bonding processes for high-end devices. The FPB series also handles several kinds of processes such as C2, C4, and FO-WLP. Last year, the company's released the FPB-1s NeoForce as the first step in the series, which specialized in chip-to-substrate processes. In recent years, 3 and 2.5 dimensional bonding applications using chip-to-wafer processes have been initiated in cutting-edge memory and logic device production, and the demand for wafer handling capability of advanced bonding equipment has been rising rapidly. By selecting either the C2W or C2S process according to changes in the bonding market, the FPB-1ws NeoForce maintains high productivity and contributes to the expansion of customers' business. At the same time, the FPB-1w NeoForce specialized in the C2W process will be added to the lineup of the FPB series, and will respond flexibly to the diversification of processes along with the arrival of the IoT age. Features of FPB-1ws NeoForce Multi-processing package bonder capable of handling Chip-to-Wafer and substrates, Capable of handling high-force and high-accuracy bonding with the company's unique non vibration system and Force Free Gantry, High-productivity and space-saving footprint by adopting multiple heads, Multi-die handling capability: Capable of handling various dies up to 4 product types with automatic selection of product-type parts Productivity/Footprint: Increased approx. 3 times (Compared with other company's models), Other Product Line-ups Wire Bonders, Die Bonders, Flip Chip Bonders.


Shinkawa Ltd. Announces Consolidated Earnings Results for the Year Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Fiscal First Half Ending September 30, 2017 and for the Fiscal Year Ending March 31, 2018
May 12 17
Shinkawa Ltd. announced consolidated earnings results for the year ended March 31, 2017. For the year, the company reported net sales of ¥16,438 million, operating income of ¥294 million, ordinary income of ¥432 million, profit attributable to owners of parent of ¥243 million or ¥13.37 per share, net cash flows used in operating activities of ¥1,252 million and return on equity was 1.2% compared to the net sales of ¥12,662 million, operating loss of ¥1,035 million, ordinary loss of ¥1,444 million, loss attributable to owners of parent of ¥1,849 million or ¥101.75 per share, net cash flows used in operating activities of ¥306 million and negative return on equity was 8.4% for the previous year. Income before income taxes was ¥478 million against loss of ¥1,744 million a year ago. Purchase of property, plant and equipment was ¥394 million against ¥269 million a year ago. Purchase of intangible assets was ¥45 million against ¥24 million a year ago. 

For the first half ending September 30, 2017, the company net sales of ¥9,600 million, operating income of ¥120 million, ordinary income of ¥110 million, profit attributable to owners of parent of ¥50 million or ¥2.75 per share.

For the fiscal year ending March 31, 2018, the company expected net sales of ¥19,500 million, operating income of ¥280 million, ordinary income of ¥320 million, profit attributable to owners of parent of ¥200 million or ¥11.01 per share.








 












